description: Angkot are smaller vans/mini-buses that serve set routes on smaller main roads in Indonesia, specially in Jakarta *different names in other area. They seat 12 people or more as many as they can,stuffing people inside it. Fares depending on the distance. Students pay cheaper for any distance. And usually passengers are blasted by funkot music or dangdut or koplo...and the Driver racing like GTA in real live...
